{"TopicId":144473,"ForumId":55,"TopicTitle":"Radial Airlocks","CreatedByName":"The Raging Sandwich","CreatedById":164377,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-24T19:18:33Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"The Raging Sandwich","CreatedById":164377,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-24T19:18:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve been thinking for a while that there should be an airlock part. This new part could be a radial part you can put anywhere on your ship. It would be useful to make ships a little more realistic. It could also be used as a backup airlock in case a solar panel or something is blocking the main one.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnyways, just a thought! Tell me your thoughts and ideas on the part below.\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"pandaman","CreatedById":130621,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-24T20:59:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOne solution to this, that was suggested elsewhere, was to make the standard and large sized docking ports also have a hatch.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"XrayLima","CreatedById":88466,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-25T13:09:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis was talked about a wee bit ago - I asked the same thing. \u00A0And they already sort of exist as an extension of a docking port part.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/136307-attachable-doors-docking-port-door/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;embedComment=2506588\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Stone Blue","CreatedById":77721,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-25T15:21:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nToo bad \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/22750-devo/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002222750\u0022 href=\u0022%7B___base_url___%7D/index.php?/profile/22750-devo/\u0022 rel=\u0022external\u0022\u003E@Devo\u003C/a\u003E had such a bad experience with someone messing with his mod hosting \u0026amp; stuff... KSP lost a great mod dev when he \u0022stepped\u0022 back... \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:(\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nBut here\u0027s his version... More of an actual radial HATCH than an \u0022airlock\u0022:\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.devogeninteractive.com/picup/image.php?id=3467_51C06F4C\u0026amp;jpg\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://www.devogeninteractive.com/picup/image.php?id=3467_51C06F4C\u0026amp;jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022image.php?id=3467_51C06F4C\u0026amp;jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/22703-023-wayland-corp-development-and-released-download-thread-new-parts/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-07-25T15:21:50Z\u0022 title=\u002207/25/2016 03:21  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 25, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Stone Blue\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbart","CreatedById":78303,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-25T15:38:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOne solution is to use a Mk I lander can and clip it into whatever you want to have an airlock. I use them all the time for that reason. It has a nice hatch the Kerbal can hold onto, and it\u0027s relative light weight (660 kg) is just right for such a purpose. You can usually offset the weight with something useful on the opposite side anyway. or mount another \u0022air lock\u0022 on the opposite side.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"pandaman","CreatedById":130621,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-25T20:45:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr you could use a radial attachment point and stick the MK1 crew cabin to it end on. \u00A0It\u0027s about the only chance you going to get to escape from one of them directly\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TheDestroyer111","CreatedById":160216,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-25T20:55:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/140743-place-anywhere-crew-hatches/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}